946539880552820742.text: How this festering berk is in charge of more than pulling on his own undercrackers I shall never fathom

946541055444385798.text: ‘Undercrackers’. Now there’s a splendid word. And new to me, at least.

946541342737526784.text:
I am from the north west.

What news from your garden Paraic?

946545196208140288.text: Jasmine persisting delicately, even at midwinter. New growth on the box hedges, though it will probably take a knock or two from the frost. And on Malus × robusta ‘Red Sentinel’, a bounty of redness. My god, that ardent, lacquered, cardinal red.

946545921822732288.text: Ooof, I just googled: like luscious garnets. Do the blackbirds come to feast?

946548863426531328.text: They don’t, funnily enough. Perhaps because they’re so busy with the sorbus. It’s longer established, and absolutely heaving with yellow jewels.
